Detailed Description

GenerateMapServer street segment item.

Streetsegment item with extra features needed when creating the map.

void GMSStreetSegmentItem::addTmpZipCode (  const char *  zipCode,
const char *  zipArea
)  [inline]
 

Will not add the same zipCode more than once, but will assume that the zipArea not is significant (will not be used in comparisons and might be null).

The strings are copied, so the caller are free to delete the strings sent as parameters.

Parameters:
zipCode The zip code to add to this street.
zipArea The postal area of the zip code. Might be null.

bool GMSStreetSegmentItem::createFromMidMif (  ifstream &  midFile,
bool  readRestOfLine = true
)  [virtual]
 

Create a gms street segment item (including nodes) from mid/mif files.

If the mid file does not have a value for any of the gms ssi's member variables, the default values are used (i.e. the values assigned to a street segment item in its constructor).

Parameters:
midFile The attribute file, from which to read values for the different member variables for this gms street segment item.
readRestOfLine If the rest of the mid line (eol) should be read or not, default true.

Reimplemented from OldItem.

virtual OldNode* GMSStreetSegmentItem::createNewNode (  DataBuffer *  dataBuffer,
uint32  nodeID
)  [inline, protected, virtual]
 

Create a new node.

The reason for this method is to make it possible for the subclasses to create subclasses to OldNode.

Warning:
Since the normal way of getting a "new" node is to ask the map for a pre-allocated one the members will not be deleted. This means that using this method to create the members will cause memory leak!
Parameters:
dataBuffer The data buffer containing the data for the new node.
nodeID The ID of the new node.
Returns:
The created node.

Reimplemented from OldRouteableItem.

vector< pair<const char*, const char*> > GMSStreetSegmentItem::m_zips [private]
 

Array with pairs of { zip_code, zip_area }, used for temporary storage during map generation.

Before the map is saved to disc, this data must collected and stored in OldZipCodeItems and OldZipAreaItems.
